transcription.text:
Speaker 1: Thanks for calling back. This is Charles.

Speaker 2: Hi, Charles. This is Arsenal Ricketts.

Speaker 1: I had purchased your pills. I had prostate cancer.

Speaker 2: And I'm trying out different things to see what I can do about getting the injections.

Speaker 1: But anyhow, I'm just looking because I've got a knee problem.

Speaker 2: And I see that you're trying to get $63.95, I think.

Speaker 1: Okay. So Ricketts in Jacksonville, Florida?

Speaker 2: Yes, it is.

Speaker 1: Okay. Gotcha.

Speaker 2: Yeah, so your prescription, when it gets written up, it does come with refills.

Speaker 1: So do you just not need this one just yet?

Speaker 2: No, no. I'm actually – no, I won't have the money.

Speaker 1: The other thing is I thought I had signed a part in your agreement

Speaker 2: where if you didn't want it, you filled a certain part out.

Speaker 1: And all I was trying to do was to test it out to see if it works

Speaker 2: because I've tried quite a few.

Speaker 1: The only thing that seems to work are the injections.

Speaker 2: Okay.

Speaker 1: Because I've tried Blue. I've tried – what's that new one?

Speaker 2: Regulin? Anyway, a new one that just came out.

Speaker 1: And no, they don't appear to work right.

Speaker 2: The only reason is that I'm living in Jacksonville

Speaker 1: and my cancer hospital is in Tennessee, Vanderbilt.

Speaker 2: Okay. Okay. So I'll refund this one. I'll make sure it's canceled as well.

Speaker 1: All right.

Speaker 2: Just good luck in the future then, brother. Okay?

Speaker 1: I appreciate you. What was your name?

Speaker 2: Charles.

Speaker 1: Charles. Oh. Like the king. All right.

Speaker 2: Like the king.

Speaker 1: I appreciate it. Thank you. Thank you.

Speaker 2: You have a good one. All right. Bye-bye.
